</section><section data-mw-section-id="26" id="mwAe0"><h2 id="Notes">Notes</h2>
<div class="reflist " style=" list-style-type: decimal;" about="#mwt143" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Reflist","href":"./Template:Reflist"},"params":{},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAe4">
<div class="mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns" typeof="mw:Extension/references" about="#mwt259" data-mw='{"name":"references","attrs":{"group":"","responsive":"1"},"body":{"html":""}}'><ol class="mw-references references"><li about="#cite_note-1" id="cite_note-1"><a href="./Mail#cite_ref-1" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-1" class="mw-reference-text">In Australia, Canada, and the U.S., "mail" is commonly used both for the postal system and for the letters, postcards, and parcels it carries; in New Zealand, "post" is more common for the postal system and "mail" for the material delivered; in the UK, "post" prevails in both senses. However, the British, American, Australian, and Canadian national postal services are called, respectively, the "<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Royal_Mail" title="Royal Mail" id="mwAe8">Royal Mail</a>", the "<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./United_States_Postal_Service" title="United States Postal Service" id="mwAfA">United States Postal Service</a>", "<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Australia_Post" title="Australia Post" id="mwAfE">Australia Post</a>", and "<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Canada_Post" title="Canada Post" id="mwAfI">Canada Post</a>"; in addition, such fixed phrases as "<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Post_office" title="Post office" id="mwAfM">post office</a>" or "<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Advertising_mail" title="Advertising mail" id="mwAfQ">junk mail</a>" are found throughout the English-speaking world.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-2" id="cite_note-2"><a href="./Mail#cite_ref-2" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-2" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation encyclopaedia" about="#mwt7" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite encyclopedia","href":"./Template:Cite_encyclopedia"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"mail, &apos;&apos;n.&apos;&apos;&lt;su